{
  "stem": "17001.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 218.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, actually those were the gendarmes, the-- the policemens.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So when we had seen that, being that my father served at the First World War, he was-- he was in First World War four years.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, when he came back, he didn't recognize his brother, because he got a new brother.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So he said that this is no good, so let's prepare.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We didn't have knapsacks, so what we did, being that my older sister, Clara had a so-called-- I can't think of the name of it now.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But before a girl gets married, they always prepare a lot of beddings and so on, so-- A dowry?",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[NON-ENGLISH]",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Something like that.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So we had a lot of damask, down covers, and pillowcases.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And in Europe, we used the big pillowcases.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So what we did, my father said we should take the big pillowcase, put the potatoes in both corner as you're holding a pillowcase up, and take a string and tie it around, and leave enough material so that you are able to sew another pillow, a smaller pillowcase that you fold up and you sew it on on both end.",
      "word_count": 61
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Then on the top of the pillowcase, you fold it over and you made like a frame.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we put the string in it.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Now, that end from the potatoes, where we sewed the material, we left it-- we swing it over, sew it on the other side.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "From this side, we sew it so it was a knapsack.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And that's where we put in a lot of clothing and a lot of different things that we needed.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So we made a knapsack for each one of us.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And we worked on it very feverishly.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
